<DocsLayout title="Custom Events - Infinity Metrics">
  <h1>Custom Events</h1>
  <p>
    Track specific user interactions and business metrics beyond page views.
  </p>

  <h2>Basic Event Tracking</h2>
  <p>Track a custom event:</p>
  <pre><code>Infinity.track('button_click', &#123;
  button_name: 'Subscribe',
  page: '/pricing'
&#125;);</code></pre>

  <h2>Event Properties</h2>
  <p>Add custom properties to events:</p>
  <pre><code>Infinity.track('purchase', &#123;
  value: 99.99,
  currency: 'USD',
  product_id: 'abc123'
&#125;);</code></pre>

  <h2>Common Use Cases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Button clicks</li>
    <li>Form submissions</li>
    <li>Video plays</li>
    <li>File downloads</li>
    <li>E-commerce purchases</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Best Practices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use descriptive event names</li>
    <li>Include relevant properties</li>
    <li>Don't track sensitive data</li>
    <li>Be consistent with naming</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Next: <a href="/docs/revenue-tracking">Revenue Tracking</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
